1
00:00:05,980 --> 00:00:08,860
[In 1983]
These belonged to Master.

2
00:00:12,620 --> 00:00:13,900
Before he passed,

3
00:00:15,060 --> 00:00:16,780
I handled the money, you kept the books.

4
00:00:17,580 --> 00:00:19,660
Now that I've left the force,

5
00:00:19,780 --> 00:00:21,060
it just isn't right for me
to stay involved.

6
00:00:21,060 --> 00:00:21,860
Right?

7
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:23,620
How about...

8
00:00:24,820 --> 00:00:25,900
How about you just
take over the whole thing?

9
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:26,940
Stop talking nonsense.

10
00:00:27,900 --> 00:00:29,820
This was a duty
Master entrusted to both of us.

11
00:00:30,060 --> 00:00:31,660
No matter what,
we have to see it through.

12
00:00:34,540 --> 00:00:35,380
Besides,

13
00:00:35,580 --> 00:00:36,980
bookkeeping and money handling

14
00:00:37,220 --> 00:00:38,340
are two separate jobs.

15
00:00:38,620 --> 00:00:39,780
How am I supposed

16
00:00:40,420 --> 00:00:41,340
to do both alone?

17
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:42,580
Listen,

18
00:00:42,660 --> 00:00:44,300
you're doing this.

19
00:00:44,340 --> 00:00:45,940
You don't have a choice.

20
00:00:45,940 --> 00:00:46,500
Come on.

21
00:00:47,260 --> 00:00:49,100
You're really forcing me
into an impossible position.

22
00:00:49,100 --> 00:00:49,980
I told you,

23
00:00:49,980 --> 00:00:51,460
I left the force.

24
00:00:51,580 --> 00:00:52,660
It just isn't appropriate

25
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:54,420
for me to stay involved.

26
00:00:54,740 --> 00:00:55,740
So what do you suggest?

27
00:00:57,100 --> 00:00:58,460
Can you really

28
00:00:58,740 --> 00:01:00,060
leave fallen officers' families behind?

29
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:01,940
Someone has to

30
00:01:02,340 --> 00:01:03,700
manage everyone's donations.

31
00:01:04,100 --> 00:01:04,900
Right?

32
00:01:06,220 --> 00:01:08,100
Though Master's gone,

33
00:01:08,380 --> 00:01:09,860
someone has to

34
00:01:09,860 --> 00:01:11,580
carry on his legacy.

35
00:01:13,580 --> 00:01:14,580
You're right.

36
00:01:17,180 --> 00:01:18,300
We'll keep at it.

37
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:20,380
You just focus on keeping the books.

38
00:01:20,980 --> 00:01:21,740
I'll figure out

39
00:01:22,460 --> 00:01:23,300
the money.

40
00:02:08,220 --> 00:02:12,920
[Double Track Puzzle]

41
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:18,960
[Adapted from Zhao Junkai's novel,
Double Track Puzzle]

42
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:23,480
[Episode 18]

43
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:29,360
[In Honored Memory
of Mr. Qian Changfeng]

44
00:03:58,420 --> 00:03:59,620
Has he been like this the whole time?

45
00:04:02,660 --> 00:04:04,100
He's been standing there
like a statue all day.

46
00:04:04,460 --> 00:04:05,980
I'm really worried
he's gonna break down.

47
00:04:12,780 --> 00:04:14,020
You two go get some rest.

48
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:15,980
I'll keep an eye on him.

49
00:04:56,780 --> 00:04:57,540
The usual spot.

50
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:00,580
We need to talk.

51
00:05:14,580 --> 00:05:15,340
Really.

52
00:05:46,460 --> 00:05:47,260
Mr. Qian

53
00:05:48,540 --> 00:05:50,300
was a man of honor.

54
00:05:50,660 --> 00:05:51,900
He's a real man.

55
00:05:54,540 --> 00:05:55,260
Yeah.

56
00:05:57,420 --> 00:05:59,620
That guy is nowhere to be found.

57
00:05:59,660 --> 00:06:01,340
We can't even get revenge.

58
00:06:02,860 --> 00:06:03,660
It's just exhausting.

59
00:06:08,020 --> 00:06:09,780
Mr. Zhang Yaohua wasn't necessarily

60
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:13,300
doing a better job than you are now.

61
00:06:14,540 --> 00:06:15,820
He was a lucky man.

62
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:17,420
He died a hero

63
00:06:18,380 --> 00:06:19,420
and became a martyr.

64
00:06:22,140 --> 00:06:23,700
It's not just him who was lucky.

65
00:06:24,260 --> 00:06:25,340
You are lucky too.

66
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:28,420
Had I known how things would turn out,

67
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:30,820
I should've gone out there with you.

68
00:06:31,620 --> 00:06:33,580
Might've become
some big shot executive, right?

69
00:06:35,260 --> 00:06:36,700
Or at least some kind of VP.

70
00:06:41,340 --> 00:06:42,380
Hey,

71
00:06:44,180 --> 00:06:46,180
you only see the success,

72
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:47,340
never the struggle.

73
00:06:47,540 --> 00:06:48,060
Right?

74
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:50,100
Do you remember

75
00:06:50,100 --> 00:06:51,500
when I first left the unit?

76
00:06:52,060 --> 00:06:52,980
I wanted to get into trucking.

77
00:06:53,620 --> 00:06:54,300
So I mortgaged my house

78
00:06:54,300 --> 00:06:55,260
and borrowed money from anyone I could.

79
00:06:55,340 --> 00:06:56,500
I asked you, didn't I?

80
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,380
You didn't lend me a dime.

81
00:06:57,820 --> 00:06:59,740
You know I had no money.

82
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:02,020
Nobody had money back then.

83
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:06,460
Finally, I scraped together enough
for a truck.

84
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:10,900
All those years on the road,

85
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,860
I saw all kinds of shady characters

86
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:16,220
and ran into
every weird situation imaginable.

87
00:07:19,140 --> 00:07:20,260
All I wanted was

88
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:25,540
to live like a decent human being.

89
00:07:28,900 --> 00:07:29,740
That was enough.

90
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:35,200
[Mengtiantang Nightclub]

91
00:07:52,740 --> 00:07:53,660
Hua, you're here.

92
00:07:53,820 --> 00:07:54,940
Get a drink for Ms. Bai.

93
00:07:54,940 --> 00:07:56,100
Come on.

94
00:07:56,940 --> 00:07:57,780
Hua, have a seat.

95
00:07:59,420 --> 00:08:00,260
Here.

96
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:03,220
What brings you here today?

97
00:08:03,620 --> 00:08:04,540
Now that you're here,

98
00:08:04,620 --> 00:08:05,700
you gotta have a good time,

99
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:06,300
alright?

100
00:08:06,420 --> 00:08:07,780
It's my place.
Feel free to enjoy yourself!

101
00:08:07,780 --> 00:08:08,380
It's on me.

102
00:08:08,620 --> 00:08:10,660
This kind of place is for young people.

103
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:12,060
It isn't really my thing.

104
00:08:12,780 --> 00:08:13,940
I missed you.

105
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:15,340
Let's have a little talk.

106
00:08:25,780 --> 00:08:26,660
Let's get out of here.

107
00:08:34,180 --> 00:08:35,500
Sure. What's this about?

108
00:08:36,100 --> 00:08:36,940
I...

109
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:39,740
have been having a lot of dreams lately.

110
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:42,460
Dreams?

111
00:08:44,220 --> 00:08:46,700
I keep dreaming about the first time
I killed someone.

112
00:08:49,340 --> 00:08:52,180
But I just can't remember how it felt.

113
00:08:54,260 --> 00:08:56,340
What was it like the first time
you killed someone?

114
00:09:05,620 --> 00:09:07,020
Mr. Qian...

115
00:09:08,940 --> 00:09:09,820
What a shame.

116
00:09:26,740 --> 00:09:28,500
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

117
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,500
You came to find me today to talk.

118
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:32,780
If we

119
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:33,780
have something to talk about,

120
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:34,940
let's talk properly.

121
00:09:35,220 --> 00:09:36,100
If not,

122
00:09:36,180 --> 00:09:37,140
don't spout nonsense here.

123
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:38,460
Get out.

124
00:09:43,140 --> 00:09:44,540
You gotta be kidding me.

125
00:09:45,380 --> 00:09:46,740
How old are you?

126
00:09:47,820 --> 00:09:49,380
Your memory's already this bad?

127
00:09:56,820 --> 00:09:57,660
I brought you

128
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:01,100
a little something.

129
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:10,660
Well?

130
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,420
Did we get your good side?

131
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:20,100
If smashing that one wasn't enough,

132
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:24,020
my boss has plenty more copies.

133
00:10:34,260 --> 00:10:35,100
Ms. Bai,

134
00:10:36,460 --> 00:10:37,540
what exactly do you want?

135
00:10:38,860 --> 00:10:39,820
I told you,

136
00:10:41,980 --> 00:10:43,860
I just wanted to talk with you.

137
00:10:46,860 --> 00:10:48,820
My boss thinks you're something

138
00:10:49,740 --> 00:10:51,140
and wants to bring you in
to make money together.

139
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:57,020
You want me to betray Mr. Han?

140
00:10:58,980 --> 00:11:00,500
You work for someone to get paid, right?

141
00:11:02,060 --> 00:11:05,100
As long as it makes you more money,

142
00:11:05,780 --> 00:11:07,860
it doesn't matter who you work for.

143
00:11:12,580 --> 00:11:13,580
I get it.

144
00:11:15,100 --> 00:11:15,700
But...

145
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:18,260
Ms. Bai, this is a bit complicated.

146
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,060
It's not just about the money.

147
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:22,460
Here's the idea.

148
00:11:24,020 --> 00:11:24,860
Give me some time.

149
00:11:25,780 --> 00:11:26,540
Let me think about it.

150
00:11:32,260 --> 00:11:32,780
Alright.

151
00:11:34,940 --> 00:11:36,260
I'll be waiting for your good news.

152
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:44,180
Don't keep me waiting.

153
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:45,500
Understood.

154
00:12:20,700 --> 00:12:21,540
Hello?

155
00:12:22,340 --> 00:12:23,140
Mr. Han,

156
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:25,020
Sanmahu got me doing all the work

157
00:12:25,740 --> 00:12:26,540
on tape.

158
00:12:27,180 --> 00:12:28,780
He just sent someone with the video
to blackmail me.

159
00:12:29,860 --> 00:12:30,900
What do they want?

160
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:32,300
Try to recruit you?

161
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:33,460
Yes.

162
00:12:33,460 --> 00:12:34,500
That's what they said.

163
00:12:35,620 --> 00:12:36,460
What are you thinking?

164
00:12:37,780 --> 00:12:39,260
Since they made the first move,

165
00:12:39,940 --> 00:12:41,100
they can't blame me for the next.

166
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:44,140
I want to handle this myself.

167
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:45,660
What do you say?

168
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:48,900
Starting from that night,

169
00:12:51,260 --> 00:12:52,740
you've already become

170
00:12:52,820 --> 00:12:54,220
Dragon Unleashed.

171
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:56,500
You're the top dog
in Xiatong's heroin circle.

172
00:13:01,460 --> 00:13:02,540
Just do whatever

173
00:13:02,860 --> 00:13:03,820
you want.

174
00:13:04,420 --> 00:13:05,460
I'll give you one piece of advice.

175
00:13:07,300 --> 00:13:08,260
Power

176
00:13:08,260 --> 00:13:10,020
only extends
as far as your blade reaches.

177
00:13:11,460 --> 00:13:12,900
If you want them to obey you,

178
00:13:13,420 --> 00:13:15,060
you have to make them fear you first.

179
00:13:15,060 --> 00:13:15,860
Understand?

180
00:13:17,140 --> 00:13:17,820
I understand.

181
00:13:47,740 --> 00:13:48,420
Ms. Bai,

182
00:13:49,660 --> 00:13:50,460
here's the thing.

183
00:13:51,020 --> 00:13:52,260
About that matter you mentioned,

184
00:13:52,540 --> 00:13:53,660
I think we can discuss the details.

185
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:54,660
Here's the idea.

186
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:56,500
How about we meet

187
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,260
at Mengtiantang tonight at ten to talk?

188
00:13:59,340 --> 00:14:01,300
I knew you were smart.

189
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:03,420
See you tonight.

190
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:04,540
Oh, Ms. Bai,

191
00:14:04,540 --> 00:14:06,020
before we've finished
talking this through,

192
00:14:06,260 --> 00:14:08,420
let's not let the bosses know, alright?

193
00:14:08,540 --> 00:14:09,540
Just come alone.

194
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:11,180
With fewer people,
the conversation is easier.

195
00:14:11,380 --> 00:14:12,020
Don't worry.

196
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:13,220
I'll be there on time.

197
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:14,340
Alright.

198
00:14:14,740 --> 00:14:15,780
Alright, see you tonight.

199
00:14:47,260 --> 00:14:47,900
Mr. Zhan.

200
00:14:48,300 --> 00:14:49,780
What's so urgent
you needed to see me right away?

201
00:14:50,980 --> 00:14:51,580
This.

202
00:14:52,740 --> 00:14:53,540
Just scoped out a few spots.

203
00:14:53,780 --> 00:14:55,900
These spots
have been really active lately.

204
00:14:56,060 --> 00:14:57,220
Haven't seen the dealer.

205
00:14:57,220 --> 00:14:58,420
They call him Mabao.

206
00:14:59,620 --> 00:15:00,620
Not bad.

207
00:15:00,620 --> 00:15:02,060
You're getting sharper by the day.

208
00:15:02,380 --> 00:15:03,180
You did this all on your own?

209
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:05,820
No way I could cover all this alone.

210
00:15:05,980 --> 00:15:06,980
Had a little help from one of my guys.

211
00:15:07,220 --> 00:15:09,220
That punk Zhong
who caused you trouble last time.

212
00:15:09,780 --> 00:15:10,500
Sun Zhongze.

213
00:15:11,220 --> 00:15:11,780
He

214
00:15:11,780 --> 00:15:12,580
is tight-lipped.

215
00:15:12,580 --> 00:15:13,820
And he gets things done.

216
00:15:14,140 --> 00:15:15,540
After that last incident,

217
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:17,100
I've been keeping him on a tight leash.

218
00:15:17,340 --> 00:15:18,140
I told him

219
00:15:18,260 --> 00:15:19,580
to stop hanging around

220
00:15:19,580 --> 00:15:21,020
with those riff-raff

221
00:15:21,060 --> 00:15:22,940
and focus on doing our job properly.

222
00:15:23,180 --> 00:15:23,740
Right?

223
00:15:26,700 --> 00:15:27,500
Our job?

224
00:15:29,900 --> 00:15:30,580
I mean

225
00:15:31,220 --> 00:15:33,060
the tasks you assigned me.

226
00:15:33,420 --> 00:15:34,140
I just had him run some errands

227
00:15:34,140 --> 00:15:35,060
when I was swamped.

228
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:38,380
If there's nothing else,
I'll be leaving.

229
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:40,740
Wait.

230
00:15:44,460 --> 00:15:46,020
You haven't been pestering me
for the funding.

231
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:48,020
Guess you're flush with cash.

232
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:50,780
Not at all.

233
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:53,180
Only because the crew's got my back.

234
00:15:53,340 --> 00:15:54,820
About the funding...

235
00:15:55,260 --> 00:15:57,180
I was too embarrassed to ask.

236
00:15:57,420 --> 00:15:59,220
If it's convenient,

237
00:16:00,020 --> 00:16:00,540
could you spare some?

238
00:16:08,260 --> 00:16:09,060
Sheng,

239
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:10,900
I brought you into this.

240
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:11,900
I'll take responsibility.

241
00:16:11,900 --> 00:16:13,060
But on the condition

242
00:16:13,660 --> 00:16:14,780
that you don't get any funny ideas.

243
00:16:14,980 --> 00:16:16,780
It's good to have a quick mind.

244
00:16:16,780 --> 00:16:17,540
But

245
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:18,780
you can be too clever

246
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:20,460
for your own good.

247
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:24,420
Understood.

248
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:28,220
Go ahead.

249
00:16:52,900 --> 00:16:53,380
Alright.

250
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:54,700
Keep watching him.

251
00:16:55,220 --> 00:16:56,140
Don't spook him.

252
00:16:56,540 --> 00:16:57,820
We're waiting for the big fish
to show up.

253
00:16:58,060 --> 00:16:58,780
Wait for my call.

254
00:16:58,980 --> 00:16:59,820
We move together.

255
00:17:01,740 --> 00:17:03,020
With Zhang Cheng's side included,

256
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:04,260
almost everyone's shown themselves.

257
00:17:04,380 --> 00:17:05,300
Except this one.

258
00:17:06,460 --> 00:17:08,660
The Mabao they mentioned
still hasn't appeared.

259
00:17:09,260 --> 00:17:11,140
Did he get wind of something and run?

260
00:17:12,180 --> 00:17:13,140
Probably not.

261
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:15,460
From when we caught that fat guy

262
00:17:15,620 --> 00:17:17,260
to him giving up Mabao,

263
00:17:17,740 --> 00:17:19,260
it was only 20 minutes.

264
00:17:19,860 --> 00:17:20,340
Here's the plan.

265
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:21,900
You two wait in the car.

266
00:17:22,340 --> 00:17:23,460
I'm going to check on Gao Buyi.

267
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:24,260
Understood.

268
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:36,780
Relax.

269
00:17:37,980 --> 00:17:38,780
Look ahead.

270
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:40,020
Smile.

271
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:41,020
Come on, smile.

272
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:42,020
Yeah.

273
00:17:42,660 --> 00:17:43,700
Listen,

274
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:45,740
if Mabao doesn't show up tonight,

275
00:17:45,780 --> 00:17:46,900
you're taking the fall.

276
00:17:47,020 --> 00:17:47,780
Got it?

277
00:17:48,460 --> 00:17:49,420
What's so surprising?

278
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:50,860
Officer,

279
00:17:51,100 --> 00:17:52,460
this counts as me
redeeming myself, right?

280
00:17:52,460 --> 00:17:53,580
We'll talk if he shows up.

281
00:17:54,340 --> 00:17:55,380
Now groove to the beat.

282
00:17:59,180 --> 00:18:00,220
Food's here.

283
00:18:00,220 --> 00:18:01,100
What are you doing here?

284
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:04,260
If I didn't come, you'd be stuck
eating cookies all day.

285
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:05,340
You'll ruin your stomachs.

286
00:18:06,020 --> 00:18:07,380
We're used to it.

287
00:18:08,100 --> 00:18:08,900
How are you guys holding up?

288
00:18:09,180 --> 00:18:10,140
How did it go?

289
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:12,180
It's getting late.

290
00:18:12,180 --> 00:18:13,300
You should head home.

291
00:18:13,340 --> 00:18:14,820
Mr. Zhan will give you an earful
if he sees you here.

292
00:18:15,340 --> 00:18:16,660
He has the nerve to lecture me?

293
00:18:17,100 --> 00:18:18,140
We're on the same team.

294
00:18:18,140 --> 00:18:18,820
But he always leaves me out

295
00:18:18,820 --> 00:18:19,740
whenever there's a mission.

296
00:18:28,060 --> 00:18:28,860
Fine.

297
00:18:29,020 --> 00:18:30,140
I'll grab you some water

298
00:18:30,140 --> 00:18:31,380
and then I'll go, alright?

299
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:06,300
Hey, Mabao.

300
00:19:07,620 --> 00:19:08,420
Where are you?

301
00:19:08,980 --> 00:19:10,020
In the booth.

302
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:10,900
Usual spot.

303
00:19:26,180 --> 00:19:26,820
Ms. Bai.

304
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:28,580
What are you doing here?

305
00:19:35,780 --> 00:19:36,740
You got any goods on you?

306
00:19:37,060 --> 00:19:38,300
Yeah. Last batch.

307
00:19:47,460 --> 00:19:48,180
What's wrong?

308
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:52,460
We might have been watched.

309
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:53,380
Split up and run.

310
00:19:56,900 --> 00:19:58,060
Nanyi, cover the back door.

311
00:20:28,380 --> 00:20:29,020
Freeze!

312
00:20:36,420 --> 00:20:37,100
Don't move!

313
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:38,420
Drop the axe!

314
00:20:38,940 --> 00:20:39,900
Put the gun down!

315
00:20:42,820 --> 00:20:43,300
Okay.

316
00:20:44,300 --> 00:20:44,780
I'm putting it down.

317
00:20:48,620 --> 00:20:49,380
It's down.

318
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:51,860
You're Mabao, right?

319
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:53,700
Mabao,

320
00:20:54,300 --> 00:20:54,940
calm down.

321
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:57,220
Put the axe down first.

322
00:20:57,740 --> 00:20:59,060
What you've done so far

323
00:20:59,180 --> 00:21:00,780
only gets you a few years inside.

324
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:03,260
But if you keep going down this path,

325
00:21:03,540 --> 00:21:04,940
you're looking at a bullet.

326
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:06,940
Don't throw your life away.

327
00:21:07,180 --> 00:21:07,700
Right?

328
00:21:09,180 --> 00:21:10,020
Put the axe down.

329
00:21:12,860 --> 00:21:13,740
Just stay calm.

330
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:17,500
Hey, Mabao.

331
00:21:17,660 --> 00:21:18,660
Why aren't you back yet?

332
00:21:19,220 --> 00:21:20,100
Go find Uncle.

333
00:21:20,580 --> 00:21:21,620
I might not make it back.

334
00:21:22,340 --> 00:21:23,140
Mabao,

335
00:21:23,540 --> 00:21:24,580
where are you?

336
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:26,380
Uncle,

337
00:21:26,940 --> 00:21:28,180
I got busted by the cops on a delivery.

338
00:21:28,980 --> 00:21:29,980
Might not make it back.

339
00:21:30,900 --> 00:21:31,740
Any way out?

340
00:21:33,940 --> 00:21:35,460
You still got any goods on you?

341
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:36,660
Yeah.

342
00:21:37,180 --> 00:21:38,460
There's no way out.

343
00:21:41,460 --> 00:21:42,060
Uncle,

344
00:21:43,180 --> 00:21:43,900
I understand.

345
00:21:44,860 --> 00:21:45,980
Take care of Magan for me.

346
00:21:59,460 --> 00:22:00,020
Han Xin.

347
00:22:00,620 --> 00:22:01,180
Han Xin.

348
00:22:01,780 --> 00:22:02,380
Ambulance.

349
00:22:02,860 --> 00:22:03,580
Call an ambulance!

350
00:24:06,180 --> 00:24:07,140
How's my daughter?

351
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:08,780
Well...

352
00:24:09,100 --> 00:24:10,540
She... She got cut.

353
00:24:11,060 --> 00:24:12,220
But we got her here in time.

354
00:24:13,220 --> 00:24:14,140
Should be okay.

355
00:24:14,580 --> 00:24:15,380
Got cut?

356
00:24:20,860 --> 00:24:21,580
Where?

357
00:24:24,620 --> 00:24:25,740
Where was she cut?

358
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:28,860
The neck.

359
00:24:30,980 --> 00:24:32,180
A cut on the neck?

360
00:24:33,060 --> 00:24:33,780
A cut on the neck,

361
00:24:33,820 --> 00:24:34,660
and you're telling me it's okay?

362
00:24:34,700 --> 00:24:36,220
Her carotid artery is in her neck!

363
00:24:36,380 --> 00:24:37,140
If it had gone any deeper...

364
00:24:38,980 --> 00:24:39,540
Tu Hongjiang,

365
00:24:40,340 --> 00:24:41,980
you promised me you'd take care of Xin!

366
00:24:42,620 --> 00:24:43,900
Are you out of your mind?

367
00:24:44,580 --> 00:24:46,380
You send her
into every dangerous operation!

368
00:24:46,940 --> 00:24:47,380
Mr. Han,

369
00:24:48,380 --> 00:24:49,420
this isn't Mr. Tu's fault.

370
00:24:50,180 --> 00:24:51,660
Han Xin is a member of the task force.

371
00:24:52,180 --> 00:24:53,540
I'm the leader of the task force.

372
00:24:54,420 --> 00:24:55,100
The responsibility is mine.

373
00:24:55,100 --> 00:24:56,000
[Emergency Intervention in Progress]

374
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:00,100
Doctor.

375
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:02,540
How... How is she?

376
00:25:03,420 --> 00:25:04,460
The wound is stitched up.

377
00:25:04,700 --> 00:25:05,500
She'll be fine.

378
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:07,140
But she lost a lot of blood.

379
00:25:07,580 --> 00:25:08,540
She needs to rest for a few days.

380
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:12,900
Thank you.

381
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:22,380
You're Mr. Zhan, right?

382
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:23,180
Yes.

383
00:25:23,700 --> 00:25:24,340
Mr. Zhan, hello.

384
00:25:24,340 --> 00:25:25,060
I'm...

385
00:25:25,860 --> 00:25:26,700
I'm Han Xin's father.

386
00:25:26,700 --> 00:25:27,540
My name is Han Weidong.

387
00:25:28,580 --> 00:25:29,700
I know my daughter's capabilities

388
00:25:29,700 --> 00:25:31,180
and her situation very well.

389
00:25:31,620 --> 00:25:33,020
I don't think she's contributing much

390
00:25:33,020 --> 00:25:33,700
to your task force.

391
00:25:33,700 --> 00:25:35,340
Can... Can you let her leave?

392
00:25:35,860 --> 00:25:37,060
She's my only daughter.

393
00:25:37,580 --> 00:25:38,300
Mr. Han,

394
00:25:39,180 --> 00:25:41,100
emotionally, I understand.

395
00:25:42,140 --> 00:25:43,300
But as her colleague,

396
00:25:44,860 --> 00:25:46,420
I can't make that decision for her.

397
00:25:46,860 --> 00:25:48,620
She's excellent and she works hard.

398
00:25:49,700 --> 00:25:50,860
If leaving the task force

399
00:25:51,260 --> 00:25:52,620
is her own wish,

400
00:25:53,660 --> 00:25:54,660
I'll respect it.

401
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:00,220
Everyone knows this job is dangerous.

402
00:26:01,660 --> 00:26:02,580
If she listened to reason,

403
00:26:02,580 --> 00:26:03,780
I would've talked her out of it.

404
00:26:04,140 --> 00:26:06,020
She wants to prove herself
more than anyone else.

405
00:26:07,460 --> 00:26:08,660
Weren't you the same?

406
00:26:08,660 --> 00:26:09,740
Are you blaming me?

407
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:11,900
It's all my fault.

408
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:14,300
My fault.

409
00:26:19,580 --> 00:26:20,380
Mr. Zhan,

410
00:26:22,100 --> 00:26:23,100
my daughter has grown up.

411
00:26:23,980 --> 00:26:24,780
I can't control her.

412
00:26:24,780 --> 00:26:26,380
I know she has her own mind.

413
00:26:28,180 --> 00:26:29,340
But she's under your command.

414
00:26:29,420 --> 00:26:30,020
Right?

415
00:26:30,620 --> 00:26:31,620
You're her superior.

416
00:26:31,620 --> 00:26:33,140
You have a responsibility

417
00:26:33,260 --> 00:26:34,580
to keep her safe, right?

418
00:26:38,060 --> 00:26:39,020
Just like

419
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:41,660
how Mr. Zhang Yaohua

420
00:26:42,380 --> 00:26:43,460
looked out for me and Tu back then.

421
00:26:55,100 --> 00:26:55,900
I'm begging you.

422
00:26:57,740 --> 00:26:59,100
I'm begging you, too, for heaven's sake.

423
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:12,300
So he had connections
with my father too.

424
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:15,500
You didn't know?

425
00:27:17,300 --> 00:27:18,020
No, I didn't.

426
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:19,900
Mr. Tu,

427
00:27:20,580 --> 00:27:21,820
when can we talk about

428
00:27:22,220 --> 00:27:23,980
what happened with my dad?

429
00:27:30,980 --> 00:27:32,540
Let's discuss that
after we wrap up this case.

430
00:28:46,980 --> 00:28:47,380
Hello?

431
00:28:48,500 --> 00:28:49,300
Mr. Jiang.

432
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:51,940
Just as you predicted,

433
00:28:52,340 --> 00:28:53,180
Bai Taohua is dead.

434
00:28:53,780 --> 00:28:54,740
Sheng did it.

435
00:28:56,380 --> 00:28:58,780
Killing can be addictive.

436
00:29:00,580 --> 00:29:02,860
Since he's so eager to prove himself,

437
00:29:03,420 --> 00:29:05,460
let's use him as the catalyst.

438
00:29:05,820 --> 00:29:08,300
Pour some gasoline on Sanmahu's fire

439
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:10,780
and make it burn even hotter.

440
00:29:11,140 --> 00:29:11,620
Understood.

441
00:29:12,780 --> 00:29:14,420
Did Mr. Qian ask

442
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:15,660
about the prescription

443
00:29:16,020 --> 00:29:17,620
before he died?

444
00:29:18,740 --> 00:29:19,140
No.

445
00:29:20,580 --> 00:29:21,700
Give me the prescription.

446
00:29:34,580 --> 00:29:35,180
Sir,

447
00:29:36,260 --> 00:29:37,220
are we still

448
00:29:37,780 --> 00:29:38,500
delivering the prescription?

449
00:30:08,820 --> 00:30:09,060
Hello?

450
00:30:10,060 --> 00:30:10,620
Mr. Jiang,

451
00:30:11,940 --> 00:30:13,100
I've arranged for the prescription
to be delivered.

452
00:30:52,500 --> 00:30:53,380
How's Han Xin?

453
00:30:55,420 --> 00:30:56,340
Why are only you two here?

454
00:30:57,020 --> 00:30:57,580
It's late.

455
00:30:57,620 --> 00:30:58,700
I sent the others to get some rest.

456
00:30:59,500 --> 00:31:00,300
Han Xin

457
00:31:01,340 --> 00:31:02,500
is out of immediate danger.

458
00:31:03,020 --> 00:31:03,900
Our people will report immediately

459
00:31:03,940 --> 00:31:05,260
if there's any change.

460
00:31:06,220 --> 00:31:07,380
What about the situation
with Bai Taohua?

461
00:31:08,900 --> 00:31:10,180
No surveillance cameras near the scene.

462
00:31:10,220 --> 00:31:11,740
No solid leads for now.

463
00:31:13,220 --> 00:31:14,420
Did we get statements from the suspects?

464
00:31:14,620 --> 00:31:15,260
Yes.

465
00:31:16,180 --> 00:31:17,180
They're all novices.

466
00:31:17,300 --> 00:31:18,580
They just spilled everything.

467
00:31:20,180 --> 00:31:20,660
Mr. Zhan.

468
00:31:21,020 --> 00:31:21,380
Sit.

469
00:31:23,220 --> 00:31:24,620
But something

470
00:31:25,260 --> 00:31:27,220
[Interrogation Record]
feels off about this.

471
00:31:28,540 --> 00:31:29,300
What do you mean?

472
00:31:30,140 --> 00:31:31,260
This raid

473
00:31:31,300 --> 00:31:32,900
felt orchestrated.

474
00:31:33,340 --> 00:31:33,780
Right.

475
00:31:35,180 --> 00:31:36,460
We hit seven spots tonight.

476
00:31:37,540 --> 00:31:38,380
Five of them

477
00:31:38,420 --> 00:31:40,580
were supplied by that dead guy, Mabao.

478
00:31:40,740 --> 00:31:42,060
The other two
were secondary distributors.

479
00:31:42,660 --> 00:31:44,500
All seven have one thing in common.

480
00:31:45,020 --> 00:31:46,620
They're all under Sanmahu.

481
00:31:46,660 --> 00:31:48,500
Dragon Unleashed wasn't involved at all.

482
00:31:48,540 --> 00:31:49,700
Combined with last time,

483
00:31:51,100 --> 00:31:52,300
it's too much of a coincidence.

484
00:31:58,540 --> 00:31:59,660
Sheng

485
00:32:00,340 --> 00:32:01,580
is playing games with me.

486
00:32:04,660 --> 00:32:06,100
The intel he gave us

487
00:32:06,140 --> 00:32:07,740
was hand-picked.

488
00:32:09,260 --> 00:32:10,380
Maybe he's being played.

489
00:32:10,420 --> 00:32:11,420
Do you think someone that cunning

490
00:32:11,820 --> 00:32:12,620
would get played?

491
00:32:14,180 --> 00:32:14,940
I think

492
00:32:15,940 --> 00:32:17,060
it's highly likely

493
00:32:17,100 --> 00:32:19,060
he's already part
of Dragon Unleashed's gang now.

494
00:32:20,300 --> 00:32:21,540
Whether it's true or not...

495
00:32:22,900 --> 00:32:23,700
Here's the plan.

496
00:32:24,500 --> 00:32:25,300
Nanyi,

497
00:32:25,540 --> 00:32:27,140
you and Gao Buyi are on him 24/7

498
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:28,580
starting tomorrow.

499
00:32:28,620 --> 00:32:30,900
Feel free to act whenever needed.

500
00:32:31,060 --> 00:32:31,420
Yes, sir.

501
00:32:36,860 --> 00:32:37,860
I've asked around.

502
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:41,620
That Sheng guy is behind

503
00:32:42,260 --> 00:32:43,940
all the recent cop raids.

504
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:47,100
And he's definitely connected

505
00:32:47,300 --> 00:32:48,780
to the deaths of Taohua and Mabao.

506
00:32:49,940 --> 00:32:51,580
I underestimated him.

507
00:32:52,180 --> 00:32:52,940
Uncle!

508
00:32:53,420 --> 00:32:55,020
Mabao didn't die for nothing, right?

509
00:33:03,700 --> 00:33:04,780
Don't worry, kid.

510
00:33:05,700 --> 00:33:07,500
I can owe others,

511
00:33:08,220 --> 00:33:09,340
but anyone who owes me

512
00:33:11,100 --> 00:33:13,020
will pay me back.

513
00:33:14,380 --> 00:33:14,900
Mr. Sanmahu,

514
00:33:15,500 --> 00:33:16,380
the heat is on.

515
00:33:17,060 --> 00:33:19,020
The cops are looking for you everywhere.

516
00:33:19,820 --> 00:33:21,700
It's not worth it to go out
and confront them head-on right now.

517
00:33:22,940 --> 00:33:23,820
Let things cool down.

518
00:33:24,460 --> 00:33:25,660
We'll find the right moment

519
00:33:25,900 --> 00:33:27,860
to settle all the scores with him.

520
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:31,100
But the problem is,
there isn't just Sheng.

521
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:33,100
There's also Han Weidong.

522
00:33:33,380 --> 00:33:34,900
If we let him off now,

523
00:33:35,140 --> 00:33:36,660
he'll push for more.

524
00:33:38,260 --> 00:33:39,420
We need to find a way

525
00:33:41,140 --> 00:33:41,940
to hurt him badly.

526
00:33:42,580 --> 00:33:43,660
What about Mr. Jiang?

527
00:33:44,180 --> 00:33:46,180
As long as we don't kill that Han guy,

528
00:33:48,660 --> 00:33:49,660
it's fine.

529
00:33:50,140 --> 00:33:51,060
Mr. Jiang

530
00:33:51,700 --> 00:33:53,540
just wants a result.

531
00:33:58,900 --> 00:33:59,860
Everyone, get ready.

532
00:34:00,180 --> 00:34:01,140
Ready,

533
00:34:01,180 --> 00:34:01,980
go!

534
00:34:02,380 --> 00:34:04,940
- Mr. Tu, welcome here
- Mr. Tu, welcome here

535
00:34:04,940 --> 00:34:07,460
- to guide the task force!
- to guide the task force!

536
00:34:08,140 --> 00:34:09,140
No, no.

537
00:34:09,580 --> 00:34:10,660
This is your meeting.

538
00:34:10,700 --> 00:34:11,940
Count me out of this.

539
00:34:12,980 --> 00:34:14,900
Mr. Xiong said you needed to
see me about something?

540
00:34:15,900 --> 00:34:17,220
Yes, Mr. Tu.

541
00:34:17,420 --> 00:34:19,580
The whole Sanmahu thing
has hit a dead end.

542
00:34:19,620 --> 00:34:21,340
So we're asking for your guidance.

543
00:34:21,780 --> 00:34:22,940
Say a few words to the team.

544
00:34:22,980 --> 00:34:23,740
Have a seat.

545
00:34:23,780 --> 00:34:24,540
We just need one final push,

546
00:34:24,580 --> 00:34:25,740
and we can't do it without you.

547
00:34:33,140 --> 00:34:34,340
Go get some tea.

548
00:34:35,940 --> 00:34:36,860
Make it the good stuff.

549
00:34:38,580 --> 00:34:40,180
Mr. Xiong called me this morning.

550
00:34:40,780 --> 00:34:42,700
Said it was Mr. Tai's idea.

551
00:34:42,740 --> 00:34:44,180
When the bosses speak,

552
00:34:44,700 --> 00:34:45,740
I listen.

553
00:34:46,740 --> 00:34:47,380
Thanks, Mr. Tu.

554
00:34:48,020 --> 00:34:48,820
Careful, it's hot.

555
00:34:49,740 --> 00:34:50,500
Alright, Mr. Tu,

556
00:34:50,740 --> 00:34:52,500
we'll cut to the chase.

557
00:34:53,340 --> 00:34:54,140
Get the files.

558
00:34:57,020 --> 00:34:58,300
Just give them to Mr. Tu.

559
00:34:58,500 --> 00:34:59,460
Right, sorry.

560
00:35:02,940 --> 00:35:03,420
Mr. Tu,

561
00:35:03,900 --> 00:35:04,960
the suspect who was shot dead last night

562
00:35:04,960 --> 00:35:06,000
[Suspect Information Form]
was Ma Shengliang.

563
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,220
From the Majia Village in the city.

564
00:35:07,220 --> 00:35:08,660
He's from the same place as Sanmahu.

565
00:35:09,300 --> 00:35:10,340
By seniority,

566
00:35:10,340 --> 00:35:11,660
he was Sanmahu's nephew.

567
00:35:11,740 --> 00:35:13,580
We also tracked the person
he was on the phone with.

568
00:35:13,580 --> 00:35:14,460
He's Ma Shengji,

569
00:35:14,460 --> 00:35:15,420
and his nickname is Magan.

570
00:35:15,420 --> 00:35:16,740
He's Ma Shengliang's younger brother.

571
00:35:16,740 --> 00:35:17,940
We asked around the village too.

572
00:35:17,940 --> 00:35:19,100
They said he went out for work.

573
00:35:19,220 --> 00:35:19,900
Couldn't get in touch with him.

574
00:35:21,340 --> 00:35:22,460
From Majia Village?

575
00:35:22,540 --> 00:35:22,980
Yes.

576
00:35:23,300 --> 00:35:24,420
That's a bit tricky.

577
00:35:25,740 --> 00:35:27,980
But at least it's a street-level issue.

578
